  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (64f779a 2022-03-20T00:11:33.074266889+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nEncountered this error while converting `require` string reverts into Solidity 0.8.4 custom errors:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57450786/159356752-3e0c4653-0a7b-46c9-8483-d65959c62fff.png)\r\n\r\nIt seems like forge is trying to parse the expected error (custom error's selector) in the first fail as a string and it ends up with those replacement characters.\r\n\r\nBelow is an example contract on how to reproduce this error. Using `forge-std` and `ds-test` just for the Vm interface and address.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.4;\r\n\r\nimport \"ds-test/test.sol\";\r\nimport \"forge-std/Vm.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract Contract {\r\n    error CustomError();\r\n\r\n    function requireStringFail() public pure {\r\n        require(false, \"Require string\");\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function customErrorFail() public pure {\r\n        revert CustomError();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract TestContract is DSTest {\r\n    Vm internal vm = Vm(HEVM_ADDRESS);\r\n    Contract internal extContract;\r\n    \r\n    function setUp() public {\r\n        extContract = new Contract();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function testExpectRevert_customError() public {\r\n        // works as intended\r\n        vm.expectRevert(Contract.CustomError.selector);\r\n        extContract.customErrorFail();\r\n\r\n        // reverts with a string while expecting a custom error\r\n        // Reason: Error != expected error: 'Require string' != '   ���'\r\n        vm.expectRevert(Contract.CustomError.selector);\r\n        extContract.requireStringFail();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // this is ok\r\n    function testExpectRevert_string() public {\r\n        // works as intended\r\n        vm.expectRevert(\"Require string\");\r\n        extContract.requireStringFail();\r\n\r\n        // reverts with a custom error while expecting a string\r\n        // Reason: Error data != expected error data: 0x09caebf3 != 0x5265717569726520737472696e67\r\n        vm.expectRevert(\"Require string\");\r\n        extContract.customErrorFail();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
